<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> have a face as long as a fiddle • have a face made of a fiddle</xh5><p> <i>have a face as long as a fiddle—</i>look dismal or extremely depressed: I saw you yesterday and you <u>had a face as long as a fiddle</u>. What was the matter with you?</p><p> <i>have a face made of a fiddle</i>—(arch.) be irresistibly attractive: A person who was well-liked <u>had a face “made of a fiddle</u>,” meaning that it was always wreathed in smiles, as a fiddle has a much-curled shape.</p> </entry>
